{% endcomment %}## Workpad bootstrap and reconciliation

Use exactly one persistent Linear comment per issue as the single source of truth
for plan, acceptance criteria, validation, and handoff notes.

1. Search the issue's active (unresolved) comments for a marker header:
   `{{ agent.workpad_heading }}`.
   - For compatibility, also reuse an existing `## Codex Workpad` or
     `## Claude Workpad` comment if present, and rewrite its header to
     `{{ agent.workpad_heading }}` while preserving the rest of the comment.
   - Ignore resolved comments while searching; only active/unresolved comments are
     eligible to be reused as the live workpad.
   - If found, reuse that comment; do not create a new workpad comment.
   - If not found, create one workpad comment and use it for all updates.
   - Persist the workpad comment ID and only write progress updates to that ID.
2. Reconcile the workpad before new edits:
   - Check off items that are already done.
   - Expand/fix the plan so it is comprehensive for current scope.
   - Ensure `Acceptance Criteria` and `Validation` are current and still make
     sense for the task.
3. Ensure the workpad includes a compact environment stamp at the top as a code
   fence line: `<host>:<abs-workdir>@<short-sha>`. Do not include metadata already
   inferable from Linear issue fields (issue ID, status, branch, PR link).
4. Keep the workpad updated after every meaningful milestone (reproduction
   captured, plan revised, code landed, validation run, feedback addressed). Never
   leave completed work unchecked.
